# Lessons to Learn — Format Template

This file is the tracked stub for `lessons.md`, which is personal and not
git-tracked. Add `lessons.md` to `.gitignore` when git is initialized.

The agent writes to `lessons.md` (not this file) when a pattern worth
internalizing surfaces. The format below is the standard entry structure.

---

## YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM TZ — [Lesson Title]

*(Run `date '+%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M %Z'` before writing. Full timestamp required —
time-between-lessons is a meaningful metric. Existing entries may show date-only.)*

**The lesson:** [One-sentence statement of the transferable principle.]

**The tell:** [How to recognize this pattern early — a linguistic or structural
signal that flags the error before it's committed.]

**The diagnostic:** [A question to ask yourself to catch it in the moment.]

**Where it appeared:** [The specific instance that surfaced the lesson — enough
context to reconstruct why it mattered.]

**Where you already solved it:** [If applicable — a prior instance where the
right move was already made. Connects the lesson to existing knowledge.]

**Domains where this recurs:** [Other contexts where the same pattern applies,
to support transfer.]
